CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 23, 1960, pg. 2 reads: "Action Still Needed - Shortly after The Courier published pictures of the condition in this area near the intersection of Francis St. and Wylie Ave., several city agencies acted to bring about removal of a lot of the junk there. However, more action is needed, because there's still much rubbish remaining.  Besides an old junked car in left foreground, there are two trailers loaded with old tires which attract youth of the neighborhood who climb the trailers and dangerously play in the tires. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Empty lot with debris, two truck trailers, one marked "Atlantic Freight Line," with tires parked on right, and houses in background, near intersection of Francis Street and Wylie Avenue, Hill District
